The paper deals with query optimization in large-scale data analytics systems, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of materialized views and query-rewrite algorithms also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the algorithmic approach used in the paper draws inspiration from nearest-neighbor searches, which is a topic in the distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
